\section{How to check if an element exists with jQuery}

We can easily check if an element exists with jQuery, by using the \texttt{length} property or by checking if the selector evaluates to \texttt{true}.

\begin{jscodeblock}
var z = $('#aTest').length;
log('z', typeof z);
z === 0 ? log('true') : log('false');
\end{jscodeblock}

                                                